00:52:59.536 --> 00:53:02.694
that show oil production versus time

00:53:02.694 --> 00:53:05.320
and how it's expected to go.

00:53:05.320 --> 00:53:09.916
And as we have, you know,
the graph shifts at times.

00:53:09.916 --> 00:53:11.590
When we started fracking,

00:53:11.590 --> 00:53:15.010
we got a lot more versions of oil.

00:53:15.010 --> 00:53:17.532
We have deepwater drilling
that's able to go on.

00:53:17.532 --> 00:53:21.770
As we make explorations, we've been able

00:53:21.770 --> 00:53:25.415
to delay the running out of fossil fuels.

00:53:25.415 --> 00:53:28.759
But that does not mean we
won't run out of fossil fuels

00:53:28.759 --> 00:53:31.150
