00:53:39.530 --> 00:53:42.911
or 2100 or sometime,
we will be out of oil.

00:53:42.911 --> 00:53:47.911
And when that happens, we will
either no longer have energy,

00:53:48.356 --> 00:53:51.640
or we will have renewable energy.

00:53:51.640 --> 00:53:54.138
And I'm pretty sure,
we're pretty smart people,

00:53:54.138 --> 00:53:57.010
we will have renewable energy.

00:53:57.010 --> 00:53:59.049
So that's where we're
going to be eventually.

00:53:59.049 --> 00:54:01.685
And the only question is
how much social disruption

00:54:01.685 --> 00:54:05.890
and how much ecologic
disruption we take to get there.

00:54:05.890 --> 00:54:08.233
So there's a really clear, obvious answer

00:54:08.233 --> 00:54:10.400
to what we do about climate change,

00:54:10.400 --> 00:54:12.331
and that's, we vest a whole lot of money

00:54:12.331 --> 00:54:15.071
in renewable resources,
because whoever develops

00:54:15.071 --> 00:54:18.461
the really efficient renewable energy,

00:54:18.461 --> 00:54:20.440
they're gonna be ruling the world

00:54:20.440 --> 00:54:22.560
when we get to this world without oil.

00:54:22.560 --> 00:54:24.550
Why don't we want that to be us?

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:26.105
And we can take that message

00:54:26.105 --> 00:54:27.930
and combine it with climate change

00:54:27.930 --> 00:54:29.681
and say, there's your solution,

00:54:29.681 --> 00:54:32.282
and it's good for the long-term
health of our country.

00:54:32.282 --> 00:54:35.680
Let's take positive action
and move in that direction.

00:54:35.680 --> 00:54:37.216
And I think, you know,

00:54:37.216 --> 00:54:41.487
why I was successful in L.A.,

00:54:41.487 --> 00:54:46.487
